title: Man's body found outside a house in western Sydney
text:
A 35-year-old man has been found dead outside a house in south-western Sydney.

His body was found on Wednesday morning after police were called to Young Street in Mount Pritchard at about 8am.

Police said the deceased man may have have been involved in a fight and had suffered head injuries.

A 35-year-old man has been found dead outside a house in south-western Sydney on Young Street, Mount Pritchard (street pictured)

The homicide squad is investigating and a crime scene has been set up.

'A post-mortem examination will be conducted in coming days to determine the cause of death and confirm the man’s identity,' a New South Wales police spokesperson said.

'Police are now conducting a canvass of the neighbourhood and believe there may have been an altercation in the home shortly before the man was found.'

Investigators are now appealing for anyone with information about this incident to call Fairfield police or Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.
description: A 35-year-old man has been found dead outside a house in south-western Sydney after police were called to Young Street in Mount Pritchard. Police believe he may have been involved in a fight.
authors: Charlie Coë For Daily Mail Australia
